Comment by Dr Ken Lam:
This is a message from Dr. Okuno with the description of their 3 cases. It
is remarkable how similar they are to the 4 cases we posted earlier. Now
that Taiwan has confirmed through postmortem that EV71 is responsible for
their outbreak, it really seals the case.
Dr. Okuno has kindly agreed to send me the EV71 strain isolated from one of
their fatal cases for our study on molecular epidemiology and virus
movement. As we mentioned in [an earlier posting, we did detect
characteristic 5'UTR sequences in our strains which are different from
other published sequences.
Perhaps others who have EV71 isolates (fatal as well as hand, foot & mouth
disease) are prepared to contribute their strains to us for sequence
analyses. I think it is important to do this in the light of our findings
as well as the fear of the virus emerging elsewhere with the approach of
warmer months in the region.
--
Ken Lam
e-mail: lamsk@medicine.med.um.edu.my
[Charlie Calisher was handling the enterovirus 71 - Taiwan thread, but has
had to go to Germany for a conference. Like Charlie, I am not so sure that
EV-71 has yet been proved to be responsible for all fatalities in these
outbreaks. No doubt retrospective case searching will turn up similar
cases, not only in East Asia but also in other countries.
More lab specimens are urgently needed, and we hope there is a good reponse
to Ken Lam's request above - Mod.JW
